#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:76
#, no-c-format
msgid "What are SCAP and &openscap;?"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:78
#, no-c-format
msgid "SCAP stands for <systemitem class=\"protocol\">Security Content Automation Protocol</systemitem> . It is a framework of specifications that support automated configuration, vulnerability scanning, and policy compliance evaluation of systems deployed in an organization. SCAP is maintained by the National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST). This framework standardizes how vulnerabilities and security configurations are communicated both to machines and humans."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:87
#, no-c-format
msgid "&openscap; is a collection of open source tools that implement the SCAP framework for Linux. The suite received the SCAP 1.2 certification by NIST in 2014."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:93
#, no-c-format
msgid "What is the &ssg;?"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:95
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <literal>&ssg;</literal> (SSG) is an open source project that provides machine-readable security policies for Linux systems. It translates established security benchmarks, such as &stig;s from the <orgname>Defense Information Systems Agency (DISA)</orgname> and <orgname>Center for Internet Security (CIS)</orgname> benchmarks, into SCAP content that can be automatically applied and verified. The <literal>&ssg;</literal> delivers XCCDF checklists, OVAL checks, and ready-to-use remediation scripts in the form of Ansible playbooks and Bash scripts."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:108
#, no-c-format
msgid "The benefits of using &openscap; and the <literal>&ssg;</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: article_openscap.xml:112
#, no-c-format
msgid "Automated auditing"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:114
#, no-c-format
msgid "The &openscap; tools, together with the <literal>&ssg;</literal> , can be used for auditing your system in an automated way."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: article_openscap.xml:121
#, no-c-format
msgid "Authoritative guidance"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:123
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <literal>&ssg;</literal> implements security guidelines recommended by respected authorities."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: article_openscap.xml:130
#, no-c-format
msgid "Machine-readable format"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:132
#, no-c-format
msgid "These security guidelines are transformed into a machine-readable format, which then can be used by &openscap; and other tools."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:141
#, no-c-format
msgid "Preparing your infrastructure before hardening &productnameshort;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:143
#, no-c-format
msgid "Before installation and hardening, you must prepare your IT infrastructure for the implementation of the &ssg;. Execute the following sequential steps:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:150
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create an inventory of the hosts on which the &ssg; will be installed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:155
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create an inventory of IT and business services that will be in the scope of the installation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:161
