#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:1196
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using external or remote resources for scanning"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1197
#, no-c-format
msgid "SCAP content may reference external resources. For example, the &ssg; uses an external OVAL file to check whether the system is up to date and patched against known security vulnerabilities. However, &openscap; can handle remote resources differently, based on the options used while invoking the <command>oscap</command> command. In addition, you can use strategies like downloading specific remote resources in advance and pointing the &openscap; tool towards the downloaded resources while invoking it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:1206
#, no-c-format
msgid "Default warning for remote resources by &openscap; while performing evaluation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1207
#, no-c-format
msgid "While evaluating SCAP content with external resources, the &openscap; tool displays a <emphasis role=\"strong\">warning</emphasis> . For example, &openscap; displays the following warning while performing the default evaluation of a system based on the &ssg;:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: article_openscap.xml:1212
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;oscap xccdf eval \\\n"
      "--profile xccdf_org.ssgproject.content_profile_stig \\\n"
      "--results ssg-sle15-xccdf-stig-results.xml \\\n"
      "/usr/share/xml/scap/ssg/content/ssg-sle15-ds.xml\n"
      "\n"
      "WARNING: Datastream component 'scap_org.open-scap_cref_pub-projects-security-oval-suse.linux.enterprise.15-\n"
      "patch.xml.bz2' points out to the remote 'https://ftp.suse.com/pub/projects/security/oval/suse.linux.enterprise.\n"
      "15-patch.xml.bz2'. Use '--fetch-remote-resources' option to download it.\n"
      "\n"
      "WARNING: Skipping 'https://ftp.suse.com/pub/projects/security/oval/suse.linux.enterprise.15-patch.xml.bz2' file\n"
      "which is referenced from datastream\n"
      "\n"
      "WARNING: Skipping ./pub-projects-security-oval-suse.linux.enterprise.15-patch.xml.bz2 file which is referenced\n"
      "from XCCDF content"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1226
#, no-c-format
msgid "The following sections describe certain strategies to force &openscap; to fetch remote resources in real time, or download them in advance and use them for evaluation and scanning the system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:1233
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fetching remote resources for evaluation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1234
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you trust your local content and the remote content it references, you can use the <option>--fetch-remote-resources</option> option to automatically download it when invoking the &openscap; tool."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: article_openscap.xml:1239
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;oscap xccdf eval \\\n"
      "--fetch-remote-resources \\\n"
      "--profile xccdf_org.ssgproject.content_profile_stig \\\n"
      "--results ssg-sle15-xccdf-stig-results.xml \\\n"
      "/usr/share/xml/scap/ssg/content/ssg-sle15-ds.xml\n"
      "\n"
      "Downloading: https://ftp.suse.com/pub/projects/security/oval/suse.linux.enterprise.15-patch.xml.bz2 ... ok\n"
      "\n"
      "--- Starting Evaluation —\n"
      "..."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1249
#, no-c-format
msgid "However, if access to the Internet is unavailable at the time of evaluation, or is considered a security risk, you can instruct &openscap; to use local files instead of remote resources."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:1256
#, no-c-format
msgid "Downloading and saving remote resources locally for evaluation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1257
#, no-c-format
msgid "On systems without Internet access, or in security-sensitive deployments where &openscap; cannot connect to the Internet, download the remote content using other tools and save it locally. You can then pass it to &openscap; as a local file using the <option>--local-files</option> option, instead of the <option>--fetch-remote-resources</option> option."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1264
#, no-c-format
msgid "For example, to prevent &openscap; from accessing the Internet but still use the patch file <link xlink:href=\"https://ftp.suse.com/pub/projects/security/oval/suse.linux.enterprise.15-patch.xml.bz2\"/> , perform the following procedure."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1272
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>(Optional)</emphasis> Create a directory for storing the downloaded remote resources."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: article_openscap.xml:1276
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;mkdir ~/scap-files <co xml:id=\"scap-files-directory\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1279
#, no-c-format
msgid "Directory to store downloaded remote resources. If you have identified a suitable directory, skip this step."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: article_openscap.xml:1290
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;wget -O ~/scap-files/pub-projects-security-oval-suse.linux.enterprise.15-patch.xml.bz2<co xml:id=\"scap-local-file\"/> \\\n"
      "https://ftp.suse.com/pub/projects/security/oval/suse.linux.enterprise.15-patch.xml.bz2<co xml:id=\"scap-remote-resource\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1306
#, no-c-format
msgid "In this example, the name of the local file is <emphasis role=\"strong\">not</emphasis> arbitrary. Notice the following information in the SCAP source data stream file available at <filename>/usr/share/xml/scap/ssg/content/ssg-sle15-ds.xml</filename> :"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: article_openscap.xml:1312
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;cat /usr/share/xml/scap/ssg/content/ssg-sle15-ds.xml | \\\n"
      "grep -n \"scap_org.open-scap_cref_pub-projects-security-oval-suse.linux.enterprise.15-patch.xml.bz2\"\n"
      "\n"
      "17:          &lt;cat:uri name=\"pub-projects-security-oval-suse.linux.enterprise.15.xml\" uri=\"#scap_org.open-scap_cref_pub-projects-security-oval-suse.linux.enterprise.15-patch.xml.bz2\"/&gt;\n"
      "25:      &lt;ds:component-ref id=\"scap_org.open-scap_cref_pub-projects-security-oval-suse.linux.enterprise.15-patch.xml.bz2\" xlink:href=\"https://ftp.suse.com/pub/projects/security/oval/suse.linux.enterprise.15-patch.xml.bz2\"/&gt;\n"
      ""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: article_openscap.xml:1324
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;oscap xccdf eval \\\n"
      " --local-files ~/scap-files \\\n"
      " --profile xccdf_org.ssgproject.content_profile_stig \\\n"
      " --results ssg-sle15-xccdf-stig-results.xml \\\n"
      " /usr/share/xml/scap/ssg/content/ssg-sle15-ds.xml\n"
      "\n"
      " WARNING: Using local file '~/scap-files/pub-projects-security-oval-suse.linux.enterprise.15-patch.xml.bz2'\n"
      " instead of 'https://ftp.suse.com/pub/projects/security/oval/suse.linux.enterprise.15-patch.xml.bz2'\n"
      "\n"
      " --- Starting Evaluation —\n"
      ""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: article_openscap.xml:1352
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;oscap xccdf generate report ssg-sle15-xccdf-stig-results.xml &gt;\n"
      "ssg-sle15-xccdf-stig-report.html"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1355
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can generate an HTML report directly using the <command>oscap xccdf eval --report</command> option, but separating the scan and the HTML report generation leads to less usage of server resources."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:1367
#, no-c-format
msgid "Scanning and auditing systems using OVAL files"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1368
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using the OVAL content files for &productnameshort; products, you can assess your &productnameshort; systems and generate reports on the RPM package names and versions that are known to be affected by security issues in published CVEs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1373
#, no-c-format
msgid "The OVAL data provided by &suse; includes the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1378
#, no-c-format
msgid "The patch-style OVAL data, which expresses all security updates on a patch level. These can include multiple CVEs per patch."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1384
#, no-c-format
msgid "The vulnerability OVAL data, which expresses security vulnerabilities on a CVE level."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1389
#, no-c-format
msgid "For detailed information on OVAL support provided by &suse;, refer to <link xlink:href=\"https://www.suse.com/support/security/oval/\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1393
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can download OVAL files provided by &suse; from <link xlink:href=\"https://ftp.suse.com/pub/projects/security/oval/\"/> . As a best practice for scanning and auditing systems using OVAL files, perform the following procedure:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1400
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>(Optional)</emphasis> Create a directory for downloading and storing remote resources."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: article_openscap.xml:1404
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;mkdir ~/oval-files <co xml:id=\"oval-files-directory\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1407
#, no-c-format
msgid "Directory to store downloaded remote resources such as OVAL patch files. If you have identified a suitable directory, skip this step."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1415
#, no-c-format
msgid "Download the remote resource and save it as a local file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: article_openscap.xml:1418
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;wget -O ~/oval-files/suse.linux.enterprise.15-patch.xml.bz2<co xml:id=\"oval-local-file\"/> \\\n"
      "https://ftp.suse.com/pub/projects/security/oval/suse.linux.enterprise.15-patch.xml.bz2<co xml:id=\"oval-remote-resource\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1423
#, no-c-format
msgid "The path to the locally saved file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1428
#, no-c-format
msgid "The remote resource to be downloaded and saved locally."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1435
#, no-c-format
msgid "Run the evaluation using the local files downloaded earlier from the remote source."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: article_openscap.xml:1438
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;oscap oval eval \\\n"
      "--results sle15-oval-results.xml \\\n"
      "~/oval-files/suse.linux.enterprise.15-patch.xml.bz2\n"
      "\n"
      "Definition oval:org.opensuse.security:def:45435: false\n"
      "Definition oval:org.opensuse.security:def:45434: false\n"
      "Definition oval:org.opensuse.security:def:45433: false\n"
      "Definition oval:org.opensuse.security:def:45432: false\n"
      "Definition oval:org.opensuse.security:def:45431: false\n"
      "Definition oval:org.opensuse.security:def:45430: false\n"
      "Definition oval:org.opensuse.security:def:45429: false\n"
      "...\n"
      "\n"
      "Evaluation done.\n"
      ""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1454
#, no-c-format
msgid "Download and use the specific files that are relevant for your &productnameshort; product version, and avoid more generic ones. Being specific about the purpose and the files helps reduce the usage of server resources such as the processor, memory, storage and bandwidth. In addition, smaller file sizes also reduce the time required to complete the evaluation. For example, if you are interested only in &productnameshort; &product-ga; SP&product-sp;, use the file available at <link xlink:href=\"https://ftp.suse.com/pub/projects/security/oval/suse.linux.enterprise.15-sp5-patch.xml.bz2\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1466
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>Optionally</emphasis> , you can generate an HTML report from the XML results file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: article_openscap.xml:1470
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;oscap oval generate report sle15-oval-results.xml &gt;\n"
      "sle15-oval-report.html"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1473
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can generate an HTML report directly using the <command>oscap oval eval --report</command> option, but separating the scan and the HTML report generation leads to less usage of server resources."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:1484
#, no-c-format
msgid "How to automatically remediate non-compliant configurations?"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1486
#, no-c-format
msgid "Beyond scanning and reporting, the <literal>&ssg;</literal> security profiles can automatically remediate the target system by applying necessary fixes."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:1492
#, no-c-format
msgid "Automatic remediation not always available"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1493
#, no-c-format
msgid "Automatic remediation is <emphasis>not</emphasis> offered in case the automatic application of a fix is too dangerous to be enforced in a running target system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:1500
#, no-c-format
msgid "&openscap; remediation process"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1501
#, no-c-format
msgid "&openscap; allows to automatically remediate target systems that have been found in a non-compliant state. This requires an XCCDF file with instructions. The overall process is as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1508
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <command>oscap</command> command-line tool performs a system scan."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1513
#, no-c-format
msgid "Each rule that fails is marked as a candidate for remediation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1518
#, no-c-format
msgid "Within the XCCDF file, <command>oscap</command> then searches for an appropriate &lt;xccdf:fix&gt; element, resolves it, prepares the environment, and executes the fix script. The fix scripts can be either Bash <filename>*.sh</filename> files or &ansible; playbook <filename>*.yml</filename> files."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1526
#, no-c-format
msgid "After the execution of the script, the respective rule is evaluated again to check if the fix was successful."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1532
#, no-c-format
msgid "All results of the remediation are stored in an output XCCDF file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:1538
#, no-c-format
msgid "&openscap; remediation options"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1539
#, no-c-format
msgid "For remediating a target system with <command>oscap</command> , you have the following options:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: article_openscap.xml:1545
#, no-c-format
msgid "Remediation on the fly"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1547
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can remediate a target system on the fly, while you are scanning it. In this case, evaluation and remediation are performed as a part of a single command. For details, see <xref linkend=\"oscap-remediate-sle-fly\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: article_openscap.xml:1555
#, no-c-format
msgid "Remediation after scanning"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1557
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can remediate a target system after you have scanned it. In the first step, the system is only evaluated, and the results are stored in the XCCDF results file. In the second step, <command>oscap</command> executes the fix scripts and verifies the result. For details, see <xref linkend=\"oscap-remediate-sle-post\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: article_openscap.xml:1566
#, no-c-format
msgid "Review mode"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1568
#, no-c-format
msgid "The review mode allows to save remediation instructions to a file for further review. The remediation content is not executed during this operation. For details, see <xref linkend=\"oscap-remediate-sle-review\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:1579
#, no-c-format
msgid "Remediating for a specific profile using shell scripts"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1580
#, no-c-format
msgid "For simple remediation of a profile without any condition, you can use the shell scripts that are shipped with the &ssg;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1586
#, no-c-format
msgid "Find the shell scripts that perform remediation without any condition:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: article_openscap.xml:1589
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;<command>ls -l /usr/share/scap-security-guide/bash/</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1590
#, no-c-format
msgid "The names of the scripts follow the format: <filename>sle15-script-<replaceable>NAME-OF-PROFILE</replaceable>.sh</filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1594
#, no-c-format
msgid "The supported profiles are as follows: <literal>stig</literal> , <literal>anssi_bp28_xxx</literal> , <literal>hipaa</literal> , <literal>pci-dss-4</literal> , and <literal>pcs-hardening</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1600
#, no-c-format
msgid "The standard profile is officially <emphasis>not supported</emphasis> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1606
#, no-c-format
msgid "Understand the format of the shell scripts and the rules within. In the scripts, each rule or recommendation maintains the following format:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1612
#, no-c-format
msgid "Starts with <literal># BEGIN fix (<replaceable>CURRENT-NUMBER</replaceable>/<replaceable>TOTAL-NUMBER-OF-RULES</replaceable>) for <replaceable>RULE-ID</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1619
#, no-c-format
msgid "Ends with <literal># END fix for <replaceable>RULE-ID</replaceable></literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:1625
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exceptions to the rule format"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1626
#, no-c-format
msgid "Certain rules contain a line ending with <literal>IS MISSING!</literal> in between the <literal>BEGIN</literal> and <literal>END</literal> lines for a rule block. These rules do not have a remediation part. You need to do remediation manually to apply them."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1635
#, no-c-format
msgid "Although the recommended approach for excluding rules from remediation is to use tailoring, you can also do it manually if there are bugs, or for tests. In that case, open the intended script with a text editor and comment out the necessary lines between <literal>BEGIN</literal> and <literal>END</literal> for a rule block."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1643
#, no-c-format
msgid "Make the script executable:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: article_openscap.xml:1646
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;<command>chmod +x sle15-script-<replaceable>NAME-OF-PROFILE</replaceable>.sh</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1649
#, no-c-format
msgid "Run the script:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: article_openscap.xml:1652
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;<command>./sle15-script-<replaceable>NAME-OF-PROFILE</replaceable>.sh</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:1658
#, no-c-format
msgid "Remediating a &productnameshort; system with <command>oscap</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1659
#, no-c-format
msgid "The following examples show how to scan and remediate &productnameshort; locally with <command>oscap</command> to comply with a certain profile."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:1664
#, no-c-format
msgid "Remediating &productnameshort; (on the fly)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1665
#, no-c-format
msgid "To remediate a system (on the fly), you can use a combination of <option>--eval</option> and <option>--remediate</option> options of the <command>oscap</command> command. In this case, the system is first scanned (audited), and then the command attempts to fix the system. During the execution of the audit, you will see the status after each rule as <literal>pass</literal> , <literal>fail</literal> , or <literal>not applicable</literal> . During the execution of the remediation, you will see the status as <literal>fixed</literal> or <literal>error</literal> after some of the rules."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:1675
#, no-c-format
msgid "Remediating &productnameshort; systems (on the fly)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: article_openscap.xml:1676
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;<command>oscap</command> xccdf eval --remediate<co xml:id=\"co-oscap-remedy-fly\"/> \\\n"
      "--profile <replaceable>stig</replaceable><co xml:id=\"co-oscap-remedy-fly-profile\"/> \\\n"
      "--results <replaceable>/tmp/results.xml</replaceable><co xml:id=\"co-oscap-remedy-fly-results\"/> \\\n"
      "--report <replaceable>/tmp/report.html</replaceable><co xml:id=\"co-oscap-remedy-fly-report\"/> \\\n"
      "--skip-rule xccdf_org.ssgproject.content_rule_accounts_authorized_local_users<co xml:id=\"co-oscap-remedy-skip-rules\"/> \\\n"
      "/usr/share/xml/scap/ssg/content/ssg-sle15-ds.xml<co xml:id=\"co-oscap-remedy-fly-ssg\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: article_openscap.xml:1682
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;<command>reboot</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1685
#, no-c-format
msgid "Calls the <command>oscap xccdf</command> module and tells it to perform an evaluation plus a remediation of the target system in one go."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1696
#, no-c-format
msgid "Saves the results of the evaluation to <replaceable>/tmp/results.xml</replaceable> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1701
#, no-c-format
msgid "Saves the report of the evaluation to <replaceable>/tmp/report.html</replaceable> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1706
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rules that you want to skip."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1711
#, no-c-format
msgid "Specifies the <literal>&ssg;</literal> policy file to use for &productnameshort; &product-ga;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1717
#, no-c-format
msgid "In the resulting <replaceable>/tmp/results.xml</replaceable> file, the first <tag class=\"element\">TestResult</tag> element shows the result of the scan <emphasis>before</emphasis> the remediation. The second <tag class=\"element\">TestResult</tag> element shows the result of the scan <emphasis>after</emphasis> applying the remediation. In the second <tag class=\"element\">TestResult</tag> element, if the result of a rule is <literal>fixed</literal> , this means that the fix was successfully applied, and this rule now passes evaluation. If the result of a rule is <literal>error</literal> , this means that the remediation for this rule was not successful, and the rule still does not pass evaluation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:1731
#, no-c-format
msgid "Usage of the <option>--skip-rule</option> option"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1732
#, no-c-format
msgid "In the above example, the <literal>--skip-rule</literal> option is optional. However, it is necessary to use it if you did not change the variable <literal>var_accounts_authorized_local_users_regex</literal> . Otherwise, you will not be able to do a <command>sudo</command> after reboot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1742
#, no-c-format
msgid "In this example, we first execute a scan and then run the remediation as the next step."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:1746
#, no-c-format
msgid "Remediating &productnameshort; (after scanning)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: article_openscap.xml:1749
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;<command>oscap</command> xccdf eval<co xml:id=\"co-oscap-remedy-post1\"/> \\\n"
      "      --profile <replaceable>stig</replaceable><co xml:id=\"co-oscap-remedy-post1-profile\"/> \\\n"
      "      --results <replaceable>/tmp/results.xml</replaceable><co xml:id=\"co-oscap-remedy-post1-results\"/> \\\n"
      "      /usr/share/xml/scap/ssg/content/ssg-sle15-ds.xml<co xml:id=\"co-oscap-remedy-post1-ssg\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1755
#, no-c-format
msgid "Calls the <command>oscap xccdf</command> module and tells it to perform an evaluation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1766
#, no-c-format
msgid "Saves the results of the evaluation as an XCCDF file to <replaceable>/tmp/results.xml</replaceable> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1782
#, no-c-format
msgid "During this step, the system is only evaluated, and the results are stored in a <tag class=\"element\">TestResult</tag> element in <replaceable>/tmp/results.xml</replaceable> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: article_openscap.xml:1789
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;<command>oscap</command> xccdf remediate<co xml:id=\"co-oscap-remedy-post2-command\"/> \\\n"
      "     --results <replaceable>/tmp/results.xml</replaceable><co xml:id=\"co-oscap-remedy-post2-results\"/> \\\n"
      "     <replaceable>/tmp/results.xml</replaceable><co xml:id=\"co-oscap-remedy-post2-ssg\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1794
#, no-c-format
msgid "Calls the <command>oscap xccdf</command> module and tells it to perform a remediation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1800
#, no-c-format
msgid "Saves the results of the remediation to <replaceable>/tmp/results.xml</replaceable> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1806
#, no-c-format
msgid "Uses the <replaceable>/tmp/results.xml</replaceable> XCCDF file from the first step (evaluation) as input file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1812
#, no-c-format
msgid "During this step, the results file from the first step is used as input for the <command>oscap</command> command. You can safely store the results from the second step in the same file that you use as the input file, <replaceable>/tmp/results.xml</replaceable> . During this run, <command>oscap</command> creates a new <tag class=\"element\">xccdf:TestResult</tag> element in the file. The new element is based on the previous one and inherits all the data. The newly created <tag class=\"element\">xccdf:TestResult</tag> element differs only in the <tag class=\"element\">rule-result</tag> elements which failed in the first run. Only for those is the remediation executed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:1828
#, no-c-format
msgid "Remediating systems using <command>oscap</command> and scripts"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1829
#, no-c-format
msgid "To remediate a system, you have to generate a script that will fix the system. You have to decide in advance the profile and type of the script&mdash;bash or &ansible;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:1834
#, no-c-format
msgid "Evaluate the system before remediation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1835
#, no-c-format
msgid "Before running the examples in this section, ensure that you have evaluated the system using the <command>oscap xccdf eval</command> commands."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:1841
#, no-c-format
msgid "Remediating &productnameshort; systems using <command>oscap</command> and bash"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: article_openscap.xml:1842
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;<command>oscap xccdf generate fix --profile stig --fetch-remote-resources \\\n"
      "--fix-type bash --output <replaceable>GENERATED-BASH-REMEDIATION-SCRIPT-NAME</replaceable>.sh \\\n"
      "/usr/share/xml/scap/ssg/content/ssg-sle15-ds.xml</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:1847
#, no-c-format
msgid "Remediating &productnameshort; systems using <command>oscap</command> and &ansible;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: article_openscap.xml:1848
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;<command>oscap xccdf generate fix --profile stig --fetch-remote-resources \\\n"
      "--fix-type ansible --output <replaceable>GENERATED-ANSIBLE-REMEDIATION-SCRIPT-NAME</replaceable>.yml \\\n"
      "/usr/share/xml/scap/ssg/content/ssg-sle15-ds.xml</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1852
#, no-c-format
msgid "After running any of the above commands, you can run the generated script to remediate the system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1859
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can also run <command>oscap</command> in review mode to store remediation instructions to a file for further review. During this operation, the remediation content is <emphasis>not</emphasis> executed. The following shows how to generate remediation instructions in the form of a shell script:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:1866
#, no-c-format
msgid "Storing &productnameshort; remediation instructions for review"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: article_openscap.xml:1867
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;<command>oscap</command> xccdf generate fix<co xml:id=\"co-oscap-generate-fix\"/> \\\n"
      "     --template urn:xccdf:fix:script:sh<co xml:id=\"co-oscap-generate-template\"/> \\\n"
      "     --profile <replaceable>stig</replaceable><co xml:id=\"co-oscap-generate-profile\"/> \\\n"
      "     --output <replaceable>my-remediation-script.sh</replaceable><co xml:id=\"co-oscap-generate-output\"/> \\\n"
      "     /usr/share/xml/scap/ssg/content/ssg-sle15-ds.xml<co xml:id=\"co-oscap-generate-ssg\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1874
#, no-c-format
msgid "Calls the <command>oscap xccdf</command> module and tells it to generate a file with remediation instructions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1880
#, no-c-format
msgid "Specifies the template to use, in this case, a shell script."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1885
#, no-c-format
msgid "Specifies the profile to use, in this case, <literal>stig</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1890
#, no-c-format
msgid "Specifies the file to which the remediation instructions are written."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1895
#, no-c-format
msgid "Specifies the <literal>&ssg;</literal> policy file to use. In this example, we use a policy file in the <literal>DataStream</literal> format that applies to &productnameshort; &product-ga;. To list all available policies, run: <command>ls -1 /usr/share/xml/scap/ssg/content/ssg-*-ds.xml</command> . For more information about a particular policy, run <command>oscap info</command> on the file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:1909
#, no-c-format
msgid "Remediating a &productnameshort; system with &ansible;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1910
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can use the &ansible; playbooks provided by the <literal>&ssg;</literal> to remediate a local system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1914
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <package>ansible</package> package is available from <literal>&ph;</literal> . Register your &productnameshort; system and enable the <literal>&ph;</literal> module. Then install the package with <command>sudo zypper in ansible</command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:1920
#, no-c-format
msgid "Remediating &productnameshort; &product-ga; with &ansible;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1921
#, no-c-format
msgid "For example, to remediate your system using the &stiga; &ansible; playbook for &productnameshort; &product-ga; provided by the <literal>&ssg;</literal> , use the following command."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:1927
#, no-c-format
msgid "System configuration changes"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1928
#, no-c-format
msgid "The following command alters the configuration of your system immediately. Make sure to test this thoroughly in a non-production system first."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: article_openscap.xml:1933
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;ansible-playbook -i \"localhost,\" -c local \\\n"
      "/usr/share/scap-security-guide/ansible/sle15-playbook-stig.yml"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1935
#, no-c-format
msgid "After the playbook has finished, you are prompted to log in to your system, which is now compliant with the chosen policy."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: article_openscap.xml:1943
#, no-c-format
msgid "Remediating for a specific profile using &ansible;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1944
#, no-c-format
msgid "For simple remediation of a profile without any condition, you can use the &ansible; playbooks that are shipped with the &ssg;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1950
#, no-c-format
msgid "List the &ansible; playbooks that are shipped with the &ssg;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: article_openscap.xml:1953
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;<command>ls -l /usr/share/scap-security-guide/ansible/</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1954
#, no-c-format
msgid "The file names are in the following format: <filename>sle15-playbook-<replaceable>NAME-OF-PROFILE</replaceable>.yml</filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1960
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create a file <filename>ansible_inventory.yml</filename> and include the following configuration snippet:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: article_openscap.xml:1964
#, no-c-format
msgid "\n"
      "all:\n"
      "  hosts:\n"
      "    localhost:\n"
      "  vars:\n"
      "    ansible_connection: local\n"
      ""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1973
#, no-c-format
msgid "Then run the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: article_openscap.xml:1976
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;<command>ansible-playbook -i ansible_inventory.yml\n"
      "sle15-playbook-<replaceable>NAME-OF-PROFILE</replaceable>.yml</command><co xml:id=\"scap-ansible\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1981
#, no-c-format
msgid "Substitute <replaceable>NAME-OF-PROFILE</replaceable> with any of the supported profiles, as seen in the file names within the directory <filename>/usr/share/scap-security-guide/ansible/</filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1988
#, no-c-format
msgid "To skip some of the rules during the execution, use the <option>--tag</option> option. You can find the tag of a specific rule by searching for the rule's tag in the playbook file. For example, to skip some rules for &productnameshort;, run the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: article_openscap.xml:1994
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;<command>ansible-playbook -i ansible_inventory.yml sle15-playbook-<replaceable>NAME-OF-PROFILE</replaceable>.yml \\\n"
      "--tags \"package_aide_installed,aide_build_database\"</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:1999
#, no-c-format
msgid "You might need to repeat the steps above more than twice, because of the following reasons:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:2005
#, no-c-format
msgid "Some of the rules require a restart of the system to take effect."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: article_openscap.xml:2010
#, no-c-format
msgid "The rules are executed in alphabetical order."
msgstr ""

